description:
Description:

Given an integer range (a, b], count the number of times digit 1 occurs in this range where a < b and is exclusive meaning it is not included in the range.

Input Format:

Two integers a, b where a<b and they signify the range (a,b], where a is exclusive.

Output Format:

A single integer representing the total number of occurrences of digit 1 in the given range

Sample Inputs:

10 25 1

Sample Outputs:

8

Explanation:

The integers that contain 1 in the range (10, 25] are 11,12,13,14,15,16,17,18,19 and 21. If you count the number of times digit '1' occurs then that would be 11 and thus you have to return that as the answer.

Constraint:

0 <= a < b <= 10^9
title: Counting Special Digit
